sec.p:
For both bivariate regressions (i.e., reconstructing temperature in CGI with PUY and GVE, as well as data from EVI and SIO for LEY), the two input variables were highly correlated (ρ(PUY, GVE) and ρ(EVI, SIO)). Therefore, one of each pair of variables was partialled out and the resulting residuals (i.e., r.PUY and r.EVI) were used instead, Eqs. 5 and 6, respectively. This was done again by applying two linear regressions followed by the calculation of the residual for each observation, Eq. 7 (PUY) and Eq. 8 (EVI), respectively.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
